1
00:00:22,643 --> 00:00:23,643
It's now or never.

2
00:00:27,565 --> 00:00:28,649
Drake Palma!

3
00:00:29,817 --> 00:00:31,527
You're my boyfriend now!

4
00:00:33,353 --> 00:00:34,104
I'm Alys.

5
00:00:34,105 --> 00:00:37,065
Alys Zyril Perez, soon to be Palma!

6
00:00:37,357 --> 00:00:38,357
Hello!

7
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,040
You’re my girlfriend.

8
00:00:41,806 --> 00:00:45,184
Act like one.

9
00:00:49,839 --> 00:00:51,257
Those girls are annoying.

10
00:00:52,803 --> 00:00:54,471
What about me? Am I not annoying?

11
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:56,473
You're annoying.

12
00:00:58,643 --> 00:00:59,644
And that’s fine.

13
00:01:01,903 --> 00:01:03,822
Dream on. You're ugly.

14
00:01:05,157 --> 00:01:06,366
You're not handsome.

15
00:01:06,976 --> 00:01:07,976
I know.

16
00:01:08,143 --> 00:01:09,183
I don't wanna be handsome.

17
00:01:10,604 --> 00:01:11,647
I just want to be loved.

18
00:01:14,283 --> 00:01:15,409
By you, perhaps.

19
00:01:19,631 --> 00:01:20,631
Tss.

20
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:22,718
Birdbrain.

21
00:01:24,636 --> 00:01:25,846
You're too much!

22
00:01:25,851 --> 00:01:26,851
Noob!

23
00:01:28,198 --> 00:01:29,198
My noob!

24
00:01:30,827 --> 00:01:32,078
I'm territorial.

25
00:01:37,334 --> 00:01:39,044
I'm territorial.

26
00:01:43,006 --> 00:01:44,216
I'm territorial.

27
00:01:47,571 --> 00:01:49,251
You told me that you
don't like me anymore.

28
00:01:49,671 --> 00:01:50,831
So, I'm trying to forget you.

29
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:53,196
But why are you making it
so damn impossible?

30
00:01:53,884 --> 00:01:54,301
I don’t —

31
00:01:54,301 --> 00:01:55,301
Shut up!

32
00:02:00,789 --> 00:02:02,149
- Seulement vous.
- Seulement vous.

33
00:02:05,076 --> 00:02:06,953
I love you, Alys Zyril Perez.

34
00:02:07,469 --> 00:02:11,932
I love you so much too,
Drake Sebastian Palma.

35
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,450
Yes. I just landed, Silly.

36
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:22,341
How are you?

37
00:03:22,343 --> 00:03:24,371
I told you, I'm fine.

38
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:25,994
It will be fine.

39
00:03:26,536 --> 00:03:27,746
Don't worry about me.

40
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:31,208
Where are you, anyway?

41
00:03:31,216 --> 00:03:32,629
I'm about to head out.

42
00:03:32,636 --> 00:03:34,116
But I'm not coming home yet.

43
00:03:34,123 --> 00:03:36,508
Because I need to pass by
the shop to meet a client.

44
00:03:36,922 --> 00:03:38,298
You're making a big step, Zy.

45
00:03:39,216 --> 00:03:40,554
And I know you’ll be fine.

46
00:03:41,351 --> 00:03:42,351
You always are.

47
00:03:43,637 --> 00:03:45,639
Thanks. So where are you headed now?

48
00:03:45,991 --> 00:03:47,701
I'm about to leave the airport.

49
00:03:49,123 --> 00:03:50,123
I'm here.

50
00:03:50,522 --> 00:03:52,399
Hurry up, I've been waiting since earlier.

51
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:55,151
I'm almost there.

52
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:57,737
I'm so excited to see you.

53
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:00,628
Me too.

54
00:04:19,856 --> 00:04:21,065
Alys Zyril Perez?

55
00:04:21,778 --> 00:04:22,612
Yes?

56
00:04:22,616 --> 00:04:24,159
Uh, I think it's the jetlag.

57
00:04:24,306 --> 00:04:26,183
We can do this later
once you’re fully awake.

58
00:04:26,410 --> 00:04:28,160
No, it's okay. I'm okay.

59
00:04:28,161 --> 00:04:29,161
Good.

60
00:04:29,812 --> 00:04:32,356
So, this will be your room.

61
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,360
Oh, Kei's not around.

62
00:04:37,646 --> 00:04:39,565
Uhm...who’s Kei?

63
00:04:39,687 --> 00:04:42,008
Oh, your parents specifically
requested for you

64
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:44,368
to be roommates with the
smartest kid in this building.

65
00:04:44,374 --> 00:04:46,527
Gosh, Mom is so mean.

66
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:50,082
But I guess this is okay, too.

67
00:04:50,609 --> 00:04:53,820
But at least someone will
help me with my assignments.

68
00:04:54,988 --> 00:04:56,281
Uhm, anyway...

69
00:04:56,490 --> 00:04:58,825
This is the list of your
books and your schedule.

70
00:04:59,842 --> 00:05:03,513
I just arrived in New York and
I'm greeted with a schedule immediately?!

71
00:05:04,089 --> 00:05:06,776
And advertising looks difficult.

72
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,871
Why did you even choose this, mommy?

73
00:05:08,895 --> 00:05:11,147
I think I'm about to die.

74
00:05:12,223 --> 00:05:13,808
And here are your keys.

75
00:05:14,601 --> 00:05:17,769
All your things are here already
so I guess I'll leave you to it.

76
00:05:17,770 --> 00:05:18,605
Good luck!

77
00:05:18,606 --> 00:05:19,606
Thank you, Ms. Rachel.

78
00:05:20,003 --> 00:05:21,004
See you around!

79
00:05:31,706 --> 00:05:33,375
It's only the two of us here.

80
00:05:36,618 --> 00:05:38,995
Is this Kei a good person?

81
00:05:41,847 --> 00:05:45,642
St. Collete, I don't want
an awful roommate.

82
00:05:46,747 --> 00:05:48,749
I hope Kei is a good girl.

83
00:05:49,927 --> 00:05:53,972
Maybe she has the same attitude
as my former schoolmate at SCA.

84
00:05:56,006 --> 00:05:58,675
St. Collete, I hope not.

85
00:08:18,736 --> 00:08:20,279
Thank you!

86
00:08:36,787 --> 00:08:38,580
Hi, Drakey Baby!

87
00:08:39,114 --> 00:08:40,221
I miss you so much already

88
00:08:40,227 --> 00:08:43,416
even though I haven't been away
from the Philippines for a week yet.

89
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,483
Why are you calling
at this time of the day?

90
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:48,111
Aren't you supposed to
be sleeping or something?

91
00:08:48,456 --> 00:08:49,457
Come on!

92
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:51,925
You're the one I missed,
and yet you're the one who's mad.

93
00:08:51,949 --> 00:08:53,075
I'm not mad.

94
00:08:53,534 --> 00:08:55,452
I'm just concerned about your welfare.

95
00:08:56,787 --> 00:09:00,290
I know it's 5 AM there
because it's 5 PM here.

96
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:02,876
But I just can't settle down here.

97
00:09:03,043 --> 00:09:04,545
I have no one to talk to.

98
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:06,797
Then talk to people.

99
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:08,215
That's what you're good at.

100
00:09:09,258 --> 00:09:10,175
Huh?

101
00:09:10,176 --> 00:09:13,095
You annoy most people,
so they become forced to talk to you.

102
00:09:14,654 --> 00:09:16,490
That's what you did
the first time I met you.

103
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:17,833
You annoyed me.

104
00:09:18,299 --> 00:09:19,726
You're really too much, Drake!

105
00:09:19,733 --> 00:09:21,469
You're still so mean to me!

106
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:25,306
I thought you'd be nicer to me
since you said I love you already.

107
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:26,983
But you're still such a meanie.

108
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:29,970
Noob.

109
00:09:30,292 --> 00:09:31,292
Hmm?

110
00:09:31,801 --> 00:09:33,761
I can see your premature boobs from here.

111
00:09:35,615 --> 00:09:37,700
Eww! You're such a pervy now, Drake!

112
00:09:37,928 --> 00:09:39,262
That’s so indecent!

113
00:09:39,321 --> 00:09:40,322
What could I do?

114
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:42,791
You tempt me so much.

115
00:09:42,808 --> 00:09:44,101
You’re unbelievable!

116
00:09:47,813 --> 00:09:50,232
So, how are you coping up?

117
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:52,633
I don't like it here.

118
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,844
There are so many blondes.

119
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:57,097
And they're all so tall.

120
00:09:57,598 --> 00:10:00,517
And most of all,
all of them are English speaking here.

121
00:10:00,532 --> 00:10:02,310
Like, straight-up English.

122
00:10:02,786 --> 00:10:04,271
Go on, laugh!

123
00:10:04,632 --> 00:10:06,175
You know, you're so mean to me.

124
00:10:06,176 --> 00:10:08,093
Ever since I left, it's like...

125
00:10:08,094 --> 00:10:09,721
You keep making fun of me!

126
00:10:09,730 --> 00:10:11,347
You don't love me anymore, do you?

127
00:10:11,357 --> 00:10:12,432
Stupid.

128
00:10:12,757 --> 00:10:13,822
Of course, I love you.

129
00:10:21,532 --> 00:10:24,118
I always wear this even if it looks weird.

130
00:10:24,425 --> 00:10:26,385
It's not! That's so cute, you know.

131
00:10:27,532 --> 00:10:28,740
Whatever.

132
00:10:28,741 --> 00:10:31,327
Anyway, did you already meet your roommate?

133
00:10:31,992 --> 00:10:35,426
Not yet. But Kei's her name.

134
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:41,057
OMG! Whichever Kei this is,
I hope she's not bitchy like Kei Chu.

135
00:10:41,633 --> 00:10:42,633
Be nice.

136
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:44,928
You'll be with her for quite some time.

137
00:10:46,926 --> 00:10:50,447
Even if you're stupid in English,
try to talk anyway.

138
00:10:50,471 --> 00:10:51,818
They won't notice your grammar.

139
00:10:52,136 --> 00:10:53,971
‘Cause they're using
wrong grammar, as well.

140
00:10:54,809 --> 00:10:55,809
Really?

141
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:01,244
I'll go now.

142
00:11:01,482 --> 00:11:03,084
- I need to help my Dad tomorrow.
- Oh!

143
00:11:03,108 --> 00:11:04,878
- Bye.
- You’re going back to sleep?

144
00:11:04,902 --> 00:11:06,111
Isn't it morning already?

145
00:11:06,725 --> 00:11:09,377
Don't sleep anymore, let's just talk.

146
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:12,838
Miss me that much, noob?

147
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:15,174
Good night.

148
00:11:15,468 --> 00:11:16,511
I love you.

149
00:11:17,304 --> 00:11:20,098
I still get giddy every time
Drake says I love you to me.

150
00:11:20,613 --> 00:11:23,616
Back then, all he would say was “Tss”.

151
00:11:24,707 --> 00:11:26,417
At least there's a variety now.

152
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,147
There's I love you and I miss you now.

153
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:33,068
See? My boyfriend is improving!

154
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:34,693
Hey.

155
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:37,405
I said I love you, where's my reply?

156
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:39,115
Fine.

157
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,617
I love you, too.

158
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,510
Bye.

159
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:20,197
I told Alys I’m leaving for US
to pursue another course.

160
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,451
But that's not the whole truth.

161
00:12:24,227 --> 00:12:25,770
The truth is I left because...

162
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:27,539
I want to forget her.

163
00:12:38,414 --> 00:12:40,625
But why am I still
thinking about you, Alys?

164
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:44,255
Tripp, you can do this.

165
00:12:44,922 --> 00:12:45,922
Baby steps.

166
00:12:46,674 --> 00:12:47,716
You'll get there.

167
00:12:48,887 --> 00:12:50,222
You need to get through this.

168
00:12:51,227 --> 00:12:54,231
Dad, why did you bring Tofer
here in New York?

169
00:12:54,701 --> 00:12:55,743
Unbelievable!

170
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:57,920
You allowed me to go to New York.

171
00:12:57,944 --> 00:12:59,404
But with this nuisance.

172
00:12:59,408 --> 00:13:01,511
Tripp, that is your cousin.

173
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:04,451
And it's better for you to have company.

174
00:13:04,461 --> 00:13:05,785
Makes it easier to move.

175
00:13:06,161 --> 00:13:07,579
It's just so not cool, Dad.

176
00:13:07,769 --> 00:13:10,915
If Drake is annoying,
I’m way more annoyed at this nobody.

177
00:13:10,939 --> 00:13:12,858
You don’t know,
but he’s such a bad influence.

178
00:13:13,089 --> 00:13:14,089
Goodness, Tripp.

179
00:13:14,508 --> 00:13:15,670
Learn to live with him.

180
00:13:16,242 --> 00:13:18,734
Bond with each other and get close to him.

181
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:22,111
Oh!

182
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:23,261
Tripp!

183
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:24,954
You'll get wrinkles faster like that!

184
00:13:24,978 --> 00:13:26,640
You should just relax, cousin!

185
00:13:27,204 --> 00:13:28,789
Just be happy, you know!

186
00:13:29,148 --> 00:13:30,148
My god.

187
00:13:32,318 --> 00:13:34,904
Dad, he just got here.

188
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:36,315
And there's all kinds of mess already.

189
00:13:36,848 --> 00:13:38,234
His trash is everywhere.

190
00:13:39,441 --> 00:13:41,151
This bastard is making me a slave.

191
00:13:41,776 --> 00:13:44,404
I am pretty sure you'll
get used to him soon.

192
00:13:45,406 --> 00:13:46,782
Ouch, that hurts, Tripp.

193
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:49,160
You only used to be like this
with Drake before.

194
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:51,230
Why are you like this with me now, too?

195
00:13:51,917 --> 00:13:54,169
So hurtful. You're mean now?

196
00:13:54,456 --> 00:13:55,874
Okay, I have to go.

197
00:13:56,281 --> 00:14:00,035
Hope your decision to go to New York
is good for you and our business.

198
00:14:01,156 --> 00:14:02,491
Hello? Hello, Dad?

199
00:14:03,314 --> 00:14:04,732
Hello?! Hey!

200
00:14:05,282 --> 00:14:06,721
Look, he hung up!

201
00:14:07,090 --> 00:14:09,342
You're so hotheaded.

202
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:11,559
You're just supposed to relax, bro.

203
00:14:12,457 --> 00:14:13,667
Relax.

204
00:14:15,412 --> 00:14:16,914
Oh! Where are you going?

205
00:14:17,415 --> 00:14:18,536
To eat.

206
00:14:18,776 --> 00:14:19,419
You coming?

207
00:14:19,443 --> 00:14:20,694
Yeah! Where are we gonna eat?

208
00:14:21,779 --> 00:14:22,859
You have so many questions.

209
00:14:23,447 --> 00:14:24,406
I said we're eating out.

210
00:14:24,407 --> 00:14:26,487
There's diner there.
It’s fine, as long as it’s food.

211
00:14:26,499 --> 00:14:27,384
Are you coming or not?

212
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:28,618
Yes, okay!

213
00:14:28,618 --> 00:14:29,785
You’re such a PMS.

214
00:14:30,079 --> 00:14:31,288
You're acting like Drake.

215
00:14:32,376 --> 00:14:33,586
One more word about Drake.

216
00:14:33,862 --> 00:14:34,881
Mention him one more time.

217
00:14:34,905 --> 00:14:36,174
I'm making you sleep outside.

218
00:14:36,198 --> 00:14:37,533
Let you freeze to death.

219
00:14:37,542 --> 00:14:38,542
Take it easy!

220
00:14:38,584 --> 00:14:39,584
You can’t take a joke.

221
00:14:40,496 --> 00:14:42,290
Oh, oh, wait!
I’m going with you!

222
00:14:42,903 --> 00:14:44,550
Aish! Kent!

223
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:46,678
You’re being too clingy!

224
00:14:46,990 --> 00:14:49,055
Ever since CB and I became classmates,

225
00:14:49,157 --> 00:14:51,119
you've been super duper clingy!

226
00:14:51,877 --> 00:14:53,911
Argh! It’s gross!

227
00:14:53,935 --> 00:14:54,519
Come on, Bee!

228
00:14:54,524 --> 00:14:56,563
Please come to my house for dinner.

229
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,147
I don’t want to!

230
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:01,609
You might introduce me to your parents.

231
00:15:01,611 --> 00:15:04,191
That's right.
That's why I'm inviting you, right?

232
00:15:05,517 --> 00:15:06,685
I don't want it even more!

233
00:15:07,151 --> 00:15:09,045
I'm not prepared for meet the parents.

234
00:15:09,069 --> 00:15:10,297
You're too much, Bee!

235
00:15:10,524 --> 00:15:12,609
You know, we've been together
for almost six months.

236
00:15:13,193 --> 00:15:14,319
And so?

237
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:17,017
What do you mean? Come on, Bee!
Say yes already, please!

238
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,627
Come to my house with me.
You can go with me.

239
00:15:20,540 --> 00:15:22,713
Aish! Come on, Kent!

240
00:15:23,487 --> 00:15:26,073
Can we just do this
next time instead? Okay?

241
00:15:27,394 --> 00:15:28,514
I don’t understand you, Aya!

242
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:33,918
Other girls want to be introduced
to their boyfriend's parents.

243
00:15:33,942 --> 00:15:35,652
But you, you don’t want to?

244
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:38,270
Whatever!

245
00:15:38,549 --> 00:15:40,064
Stay with that Sheen of yours!

246
00:15:43,417 --> 00:15:44,417
Bee!

247
00:15:45,404 --> 00:15:47,572
- Ugh!
- Bee!

248
00:15:48,190 --> 00:15:49,775
Okay. Say cheese!

249
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:52,384
Cheese.

250
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,720
Hold on.

251
00:15:56,139 --> 00:15:57,139
Drake...

252
00:15:58,233 --> 00:15:59,317
Fix your smile.

253
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,812
You look like you're smiling at a funeral.

254
00:16:00,813 --> 00:16:02,273
I told you it's for a pictorial.

255
00:16:03,386 --> 00:16:04,387
This is how I smile.

256
00:16:05,071 --> 00:16:07,365
If you don't like,
I can just go to my room.

257
00:16:07,827 --> 00:16:08,827
Just smile!

258
00:16:11,565 --> 00:16:12,108
Alright!

259
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,885
One more. Say cheese!

260
00:16:15,109 --> 00:16:16,109
Cheese.

261
00:16:16,657 --> 00:16:19,228
Okay. Next is the family.

262
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,278
Drake, smile.

263
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:38,469
I wonder if my brother would like me.

264
00:16:38,928 --> 00:16:41,013
I think I'll make a really cool brother.

265
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:44,002
I'm waiting for Ethos already.

266
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,663
I want to meet him already.

267
00:16:46,164 --> 00:16:48,207
But I also want to have my own baby.

268
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:50,835
But I should wait.

269
00:16:51,509 --> 00:16:52,635
Everybody say cheese!

270
00:16:52,942 --> 00:16:54,318
Cheese!

271
00:16:57,084 --> 00:16:58,460
Come on, Alys, pick up.

272
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,144
Why aren't you picking up?

273
00:17:00,815 --> 00:17:02,275
Did she get into trouble again?

274
00:17:02,350 --> 00:17:02,851
Drake...

275
00:17:02,876 --> 00:17:03,876
That troublemaker —

276
00:17:05,189 --> 00:17:06,189
What?

277
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:10,204
I know you want to go to New York.

278
00:17:10,505 --> 00:17:12,298
Yes, Dad. Can I go now?

279
00:17:15,439 --> 00:17:17,858
Come on, Dad. This isn't fair.

280
00:17:18,134 --> 00:17:19,593
I've been following you around.

281
00:17:20,034 --> 00:17:21,160
I agreed to this photoshoot.

282
00:17:21,161 --> 00:17:22,688
I even agreed to wear this shirt.

283
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:24,792
I even agreed to sign those damned papers

284
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:27,921
saying that I won't get my inheritance
if I take my studies for granted.

285
00:17:28,093 --> 00:17:29,853
I've been practically
licking your ass, Dad.

286
00:17:30,419 --> 00:17:31,419
Calm down, son.

287
00:17:31,795 --> 00:17:32,795
I have a deal for you.

288
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:34,302
What now?

289
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:36,805
Take your APE.

290
00:17:37,793 --> 00:17:40,713
If you pass and finish it,
I’ll allow you to take a vacation.

291
00:17:41,111 --> 00:17:42,695
But your vacation's only for a week.

292
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:46,677
Easy. Prepare my tickets now, Dad.

293
00:17:47,469 --> 00:17:48,469
Is that for real?

294
00:17:49,171 --> 00:17:50,171
I'm a genius, Dad.

295
00:17:50,549 --> 00:17:52,113
I thought you knew that already.

296
00:17:52,563 --> 00:17:54,782
I'll go now. I need to study.

297
00:18:22,150 --> 00:18:23,853
What to do now, Alys?

298
00:18:24,643 --> 00:18:26,981
St. Collete, pray for me.

299
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:29,775
I don't even like my advertising course.

300
00:18:30,276 --> 00:18:32,637
And why is it even in New York?

301
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:34,843
I'm so far from my comfort zone.

302
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:37,346
And I'm also LDR with Drake.

303
00:18:38,639 --> 00:18:41,308
But maybe I do need this.

304
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:43,602
What even is four years?

305
00:18:44,205 --> 00:18:44,789
Hmp!

306
00:18:45,258 --> 00:18:48,168
I'll prove to mommy and
myself that I can do this!

307
00:18:48,804 --> 00:18:51,473
You can do this, Alys! Let's go!

308
00:18:54,013 --> 00:18:55,097
I miss you, Alys.

309
00:18:55,886 --> 00:18:57,513
I miss you already.

310
00:18:58,054 --> 00:19:00,807
But I think this has to happen.

311
00:19:01,646 --> 00:19:04,357
For now, I will do my best here.

312
00:19:04,976 --> 00:19:07,188
Get myself a good career.

313
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:09,873
So I can build a family with you.

314
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,794
And yes, I’ll visit you soon.

315
00:19:20,009 --> 00:19:22,929
I miss you badly, my Noob.

316
00:19:27,331 --> 00:19:28,999
How can I move on from you, Alys?

317
00:19:30,178 --> 00:19:31,846
You're so difficult to forget.

318
00:19:32,744 --> 00:19:37,457
Maybe since I'm so far from you,
it'll be easier.

319
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:39,960
I'll just focus on myself first.

320
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:44,350
Good morning, New York!

321
00:19:44,364 --> 00:19:47,785
This is your morning weather update
from a city that never sleeps!

322
00:19:48,035 --> 00:19:51,166
We’ve got cold temperatures to
kick things off this morning.

323
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,483
Plenty of fresh spring air,
across the city.

324
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:54,484
Alys!

325
00:19:55,402 --> 00:19:56,402
Alys!

326
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,029
Wake up!

327
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:00,616
What the heck is wrong with you?!

328
00:20:05,052 --> 00:20:05,720
Kei?

329
00:20:05,745 --> 00:20:06,745
Get up!

330
00:20:07,096 --> 00:20:08,222
Kei, is that you?

331
00:20:10,558 --> 00:20:11,558
Look!

332
00:20:16,355 --> 00:20:17,815
Alys Zyril Perez.

333
00:20:18,816 --> 00:20:19,976
Are you even listening to me?

334
00:20:20,735 --> 00:20:21,735
Why?

335
00:20:22,399 --> 00:20:23,399
What is it?

336
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,200
What?

337
00:20:27,412 --> 00:20:28,997
Should I just toss these plates?

338
00:20:30,643 --> 00:20:32,353
Oh, sorry.

339
00:20:34,158 --> 00:20:35,918
Sorry, Kei.

340
00:20:35,932 --> 00:20:38,488
I don't know how to wash the dishes.

341
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:40,071
How do I do it?

342
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:42,616
God! You're hopeless!

343
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:44,618
Why are you even here?

344
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:47,579
To study?

345
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,421
Are you kidding me?

346
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:57,423
You, Alys Zyril Perez?

347
00:20:57,819 --> 00:20:59,029
The lowest in our batch?

348
00:21:00,353 --> 00:21:01,938
You're too much, Kei!

349
00:21:02,113 --> 00:21:04,156
My grades were high last semester!

350
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:10,686
OMG. Kei is super pretty now!

351
00:21:13,228 --> 00:21:16,398
Huhu, I want to be like that, too!

352
00:21:19,276 --> 00:21:20,276
What?!

353
00:21:39,577 --> 00:21:41,133
I'm sorry, Kei.

354
00:21:41,137 --> 00:21:42,956
I'll just buy disposables.

355
00:21:43,744 --> 00:21:44,745
Whatever!

356
00:21:56,114 --> 00:21:57,114
Kei?

357
00:21:57,313 --> 00:21:58,313
What?

358
00:21:59,289 --> 00:22:01,041
What's your course?

359
00:22:04,413 --> 00:22:05,414
First, Alys.

360
00:22:06,171 --> 00:22:08,424
The term course refers to the subject.

361
00:22:09,013 --> 00:22:12,224
The proper question is,
what is your degree program?

362
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:16,252
Oh, so that's how it is.

363
00:22:16,611 --> 00:22:19,318
So, what's your degree program?

364
00:22:19,797 --> 00:22:22,717
Advertising. I started last semester.

365
00:22:23,477 --> 00:22:24,718
Oh! Same!

366
00:22:24,724 --> 00:22:26,262
I'm advertising, too!

367
00:22:26,271 --> 00:22:28,055
But it's just my first sem.

368
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,892
Do you have nothing better to do?

369
00:22:32,926 --> 00:22:35,208
Kei, it's too early for you to study.

370
00:22:35,215 --> 00:22:37,315
Let's go jogging at Central Park.

371
00:22:41,095 --> 00:22:42,778
In this weather?

372
00:22:44,609 --> 00:22:45,693
No, thank you.

373
00:22:51,029 --> 00:22:52,204
Okay.

374
00:22:52,238 --> 00:22:53,239
Super short-tempered.

375
00:22:59,777 --> 00:23:02,113
Tripp! Come on! Wake up!

376
00:23:02,117 --> 00:23:04,119
Wake up! Let's go!
Let's go walk around NYCU!

377
00:23:05,690 --> 00:23:07,918
Tripp, come on! Let's go!

378
00:23:07,942 --> 00:23:09,513
Come with me!

379
00:23:09,870 --> 00:23:10,870
My god.

380
00:23:10,895 --> 00:23:12,432
Just go to your mom's house!

381
00:23:13,165 --> 00:23:15,667
You have a house!
Yet you want to take up space here.

382
00:23:16,235 --> 00:23:19,106
Come on! Come on, please!

383
00:23:19,122 --> 00:23:22,301
Let’s go, come on! Come with me!

384
00:23:22,308 --> 00:23:23,527
- Come with me!
- Stop it!

385
00:23:25,090 --> 00:23:27,050
I said I don't want to!
Leave by yourself!

386
00:23:28,327 --> 00:23:31,247
I just want to sleep.
Don't you understand?

387
00:23:32,256 --> 00:23:33,257
What’s wrong with you?

388
00:23:39,806 --> 00:23:40,806
Tss!

389
00:23:40,813 --> 00:23:41,980
What's his problem?

390
00:23:42,004 --> 00:23:43,364
And he has the nerve to get angry.

391
00:23:49,303 --> 00:23:53,182
Meanwhile, my class will start in a day.

392
00:23:53,327 --> 00:23:54,327
Feeling nervous.

393
00:23:55,254 --> 00:23:56,547
I don’t know anyone here.

394
00:23:57,327 --> 00:23:58,453
I have no friends.

395
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:01,460
The people at NYCU are smart.

396
00:24:02,294 --> 00:24:03,574
That's why I need to do my best.

397
00:24:04,746 --> 00:24:05,714
I have to study hard.

398
00:24:05,715 --> 00:24:07,696
So that when I go back to the Philippines,

399
00:24:08,493 --> 00:24:09,785
I’ll be better than Drake.

400
00:24:11,245 --> 00:24:12,565
That's all I really want, anyway.

401
00:24:13,785 --> 00:24:15,412
Because Zyril is already with him.

402
00:24:17,778 --> 00:24:18,779
Goodness, Tripp.

403
00:24:19,969 --> 00:24:21,721
When will this end?

404
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:36,891
Good morning, New York!

405
00:24:38,452 --> 00:24:39,452
Good morning, Rachel!

406
00:24:39,453 --> 00:24:40,787
Good morning, Ms. Perez!

407
00:24:42,185 --> 00:24:43,186
Good morning!

408
00:25:07,312 --> 00:25:09,064
Hi, Drakey Baby!

409
00:25:09,564 --> 00:25:11,010
Tss. Missed me?

410
00:25:11,012 --> 00:25:12,178
Of course!

411
00:25:13,052 --> 00:25:14,863
Did you miss me, too?

412
00:25:14,887 --> 00:25:15,887
I don't know.

413
00:25:15,911 --> 00:25:17,890
I'm liking this set up, actually.

414
00:25:18,369 --> 00:25:19,369
Huh?

415
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:20,643
But why?

416
00:25:21,029 --> 00:25:23,156
Don't you want to see me?

417
00:25:23,316 --> 00:25:24,526
Good morning!

418
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:26,232
Good morning!

419
00:25:27,529 --> 00:25:28,529
Yes.

420
00:25:29,109 --> 00:25:30,986
Because I'm tempted when I'm near you.

421
00:25:32,029 --> 00:25:34,450
Goodness, Drake Sebastian Palma!

422
00:25:34,823 --> 00:25:37,411
Are you really only after my body?

423
00:25:37,659 --> 00:25:38,035
Joke!

424
00:25:38,077 --> 00:25:39,077
Look at this guy.

425
00:25:39,248 --> 00:25:42,392
Ever since I left,
he's been laughing all the time.

426
00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:44,752
I think I'm really turning into a comedian.

427
00:25:45,654 --> 00:25:48,157
I've just been busy.
I've been with my dad all day.

428
00:25:48,526 --> 00:25:49,526
How have you been?

429
00:25:50,179 --> 00:25:51,889
Just out on a jog.

430
00:25:52,181 --> 00:25:53,808
This is actually tiring.

431
00:25:54,183 --> 00:25:54,934
Stupid.

432
00:25:55,017 --> 00:25:56,017
Of course!

433
00:25:56,232 --> 00:25:57,817
Did you meet your roommate already?

434
00:25:57,890 --> 00:26:00,059
Yes, it's Kei Chui!

435
00:26:00,536 --> 00:26:01,536
Amazing, right?

436
00:26:01,816 --> 00:26:03,683
The world's so small!

437
00:26:03,696 --> 00:26:05,956
Did it surprise you?
I got surprised, too.

438
00:26:06,243 --> 00:26:07,285
Hello, Drake?

439
00:26:07,744 --> 00:26:08,870
Are you still there?

440
00:26:09,788 --> 00:26:10,580
Yes.

441
00:26:10,581 --> 00:26:11,581
What were you saying?

442
00:26:11,997 --> 00:26:13,165
Nothing.

443
00:26:13,364 --> 00:26:16,742
I said my roommate is Kei Chui.

444
00:26:17,037 --> 00:26:18,330
Kei seems good.

445
00:26:18,802 --> 00:26:20,178
You should befriend her.

446
00:26:20,554 --> 00:26:21,805
You think so?

447
00:26:23,342 --> 00:26:24,342
Drake?

448
00:26:24,349 --> 00:26:25,349
Hmm?

449
00:26:25,622 --> 00:26:27,082
Can you go on a vacation here?

450
00:26:27,089 --> 00:26:28,590
Even just for a week.

451
00:26:28,614 --> 00:26:29,907
Please?

452
00:26:32,441 --> 00:26:33,150
Drake!

453
00:26:33,442 --> 00:26:36,129
I said I'll visit you on Thanksgiving.

454
00:26:36,153 --> 00:26:37,452
Can't wait?

455
00:26:37,476 --> 00:26:38,769
No! Because —

456
00:26:40,646 --> 00:26:41,313
Huh?

457
00:26:41,556 --> 00:26:43,933
What happened?
Why did it disappear?

458
00:26:48,317 --> 00:26:50,277
Will Drake and I work out?

459
00:26:50,609 --> 00:26:53,904
I mean, they say LDR is hard, right?

460
00:26:54,784 --> 00:26:56,744
Ugh, annoying!

461
00:26:59,025 --> 00:27:00,735
Gosh! It really won’t work —

462
00:27:08,281 --> 00:27:09,449
Come on!

463
00:27:10,325 --> 00:27:11,868
What the hell?!

464
00:27:13,995 --> 00:27:15,121
She’s in a bad mood.

465
00:27:19,136 --> 00:27:20,136
Zy?

466
00:27:21,930 --> 00:27:22,930
Zy?

467
00:27:24,329 --> 00:27:25,329
How so?

468
00:27:25,596 --> 00:27:27,196
She’s supposed to be in the Philippines.

469
00:27:27,836 --> 00:27:30,436
What would she be doing here?
She is really crazy about my cousin.

470
00:27:32,289 --> 00:27:33,916
Oh man, I really don’t know!

471
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:36,071
Life is so weird.

472
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:37,821
Focus, Tripp.

473
00:27:38,223 --> 00:27:39,867
You're here to study.

474
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:41,600
Let's just go to school.

475
00:27:55,448 --> 00:27:57,204
Hey! Watch it!

476
00:27:57,228 --> 00:27:58,228
Sorry.

477
00:27:58,628 --> 00:28:00,004
Be thankful you're pretty.

478
00:28:00,554 --> 00:28:01,764
I know, right?

479
00:28:03,224 --> 00:28:04,350
I thought she was American?

480
00:28:06,394 --> 00:28:08,020
Life is so weird.

481
00:28:09,522 --> 00:28:11,691
Such a cool new hair color!

482
00:28:11,874 --> 00:28:13,126
Bee, look!

483
00:28:13,841 --> 00:28:14,841
Bee!

484
00:28:15,759 --> 00:28:18,262
Bee, my hair is so beautiful.
Look at it!

485
00:28:18,995 --> 00:28:19,995
Bee.

486
00:28:27,252 --> 00:28:30,338
Kent, come on.
You're sulking too much.

487
00:28:31,566 --> 00:28:34,194
I just didn't attend the dinner.

488
00:28:34,467 --> 00:28:37,429
My reason is valid! I’m scared!

489
00:28:43,810 --> 00:28:46,396
Bee, are you taking summer classes?

490
00:28:49,010 --> 00:28:52,471
I thought we were
visiting bestie in New York?

491
00:29:04,497 --> 00:29:05,498
Bee...

492
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:10,164
I'm sorry.

493
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:13,350
You know, Aya.

494
00:29:14,012 --> 00:29:16,640
You're the only girl that lasted
this long with me, right?

495
00:29:18,512 --> 00:29:20,596
I just want to introduce you to my parents.

496
00:29:20,597 --> 00:29:21,932
Why don't you want to?

497
00:29:23,378 --> 00:29:24,712
Because, Kent...

498
00:29:26,305 --> 00:29:27,682
Are you sure?

499
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,244
You’ll introduce me?

500
00:29:30,422 --> 00:29:31,924
I mean, me?

501
00:29:32,453 --> 00:29:34,064
Gabriella Pineda?

502
00:29:35,022 --> 00:29:35,982
Are you serious?

503
00:29:35,983 --> 00:29:38,860
You're going to introduce
me to your parents?

504
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:41,154
And why should they be scared of you?

505
00:29:42,042 --> 00:29:43,669
Because you look like a gangster?

506
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:46,285
Or because sometimes you go crazy?

507
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:49,246
Or because sometimes you
punch people out of nowhere?

508
00:29:51,468 --> 00:29:53,595
They shouldn’t be scared of you, right?

509
00:29:56,573 --> 00:29:58,951
Do you want us not to reach seven months?

510
00:29:59,284 --> 00:30:00,493
I'll break up with you!

511
00:30:00,494 --> 00:30:01,870
Right here, right now!

512
00:30:01,875 --> 00:30:02,875
Huh?

513
00:30:05,712 --> 00:30:07,464
- Ouch!
- You always use that to scare me!

514
00:30:11,286 --> 00:30:12,286
Well, because...

515
00:30:13,072 --> 00:30:15,157
that's the only thing that scares you.

516
00:30:16,326 --> 00:30:20,288
That's because Kent loves Aya very much.

517
00:30:21,856 --> 00:30:22,856
Right?

518
00:30:23,116 --> 00:30:24,159
I don't know with you.

519
00:30:24,243 --> 00:30:26,158
I'll just schedule my flight.

520
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:30,370
Are you really going?

521
00:30:36,505 --> 00:30:38,461
I really want to go, Bee, but...

522
00:30:39,092 --> 00:30:40,961
I need to attend summer classes.

523
00:30:40,985 --> 00:30:43,821
The subject wasn't offered
to me back in first sem.

524
00:30:44,716 --> 00:30:47,844
I'll fall behind the curriculum
if I don't take it this summer.

525
00:30:49,679 --> 00:30:50,752
Alright.

526
00:30:50,776 --> 00:30:52,599
It looks like I can’t do anything about it.

527
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:55,586
Just promise me, Bee!

528
00:30:55,689 --> 00:30:58,523
You won't fall for Sheen
while you're there in the U.S.

529
00:30:58,779 --> 00:31:00,280
You know too much, Kent!

530
00:31:00,609 --> 00:31:01,711
Leave me alone!

531
00:31:01,735 --> 00:31:03,592
Bee, promise me!

532
00:31:03,596 --> 00:31:04,777
Stop it!

533
00:31:06,036 --> 00:31:07,663
Stop, you’re talking nonsense!

534
00:31:11,041 --> 00:31:12,084
Stay there.

535
00:31:22,273 --> 00:31:23,899
I'll miss you.

536
00:31:25,824 --> 00:31:26,825
Really?

537
00:31:28,206 --> 00:31:29,206
Mmm.

538
00:31:33,490 --> 00:31:36,827
Me too, I’ll miss you.

539
00:31:40,088 --> 00:31:41,840
Come with us, please?

540
00:31:47,965 --> 00:31:48,966
How was the exam?

541
00:31:52,606 --> 00:31:53,732
It was easy.

542
00:31:54,615 --> 00:31:55,699
When's the result?

543
00:31:56,095 --> 00:31:57,137
I don't know.

544
00:31:57,308 --> 00:31:58,684
But I'm sure I aced it.

545
00:31:59,324 --> 00:32:01,535
Some of the questions,
I've already read it somewhere.

546
00:32:02,313 --> 00:32:03,981
That's why I love reading, Dad.

547
00:32:04,738 --> 00:32:06,196
Your Aunt Katrina's not here.

548
00:32:06,197 --> 00:32:07,449
Come eat with me instead.

549
00:32:12,614 --> 00:32:16,994
Your Uncle Tristan said Tripp and
Tofer are living at his flat.

550
00:32:17,229 --> 00:32:17,897
Tofer?

551
00:32:18,123 --> 00:32:19,500
That annoying guy?

552
00:32:20,162 --> 00:32:21,413
You're so mean to your cousin!

553
00:32:22,158 --> 00:32:23,701
He's so loud and annoying.

554
00:32:24,645 --> 00:32:26,564
Tripp is probably getting
annoyed with him too.

555
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:29,907
Serves him right for
being there while I'm here.

556
00:32:32,208 --> 00:32:34,461
Alys’ dorm is close there.

557
00:32:34,756 --> 00:32:36,636
Wait, you do know she’s
living in a dorm, right?

558
00:32:37,373 --> 00:32:40,084
It's great that Alys got high grades.

559
00:32:40,347 --> 00:32:41,973
That's why she got in at NYCU.

560
00:32:42,166 --> 00:32:45,419
The papers and essay that
Andy and Dana made are good.

561
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:46,821
And so?

562
00:32:49,290 --> 00:32:50,333
Nothing, Drake.

563
00:32:50,487 --> 00:32:51,571
I just wanted to tell you.

564
00:32:52,014 --> 00:32:54,600
Even if you’re so smart
and you graduated,

565
00:32:55,185 --> 00:32:56,825
I still want you here in the Philippines.

566
00:32:56,983 --> 00:32:58,568
I don't want us to be apart.

567
00:32:59,175 --> 00:33:00,175
Clingy.

568
00:33:00,741 --> 00:33:01,980
You're disgusting, Dad.

569
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:03,815
You’re so cute, Drake.

570
00:33:05,275 --> 00:33:07,861
Let’s eat.
We barely even spend time together anymore.

571
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:31,259
Hey, is someone sitting here?

572
00:33:31,941 --> 00:33:33,902
- Huh?
- Is someone sitting here?

573
00:33:34,777 --> 00:33:35,777
What? I'm sorry?

574
00:33:35,778 --> 00:33:36,779
Is someone sitting here?

575
00:33:37,481 --> 00:33:39,399
- Uh, no one is.
- Okay.

576
00:33:43,258 --> 00:33:44,634
Are you new here?

577
00:33:44,739 --> 00:33:45,739
Uhm...

578
00:33:45,745 --> 00:33:46,745
I'm Karen.

579
00:33:46,996 --> 00:33:49,337
Yeah. I'm Alys Zyril Perez.

580
00:33:49,361 --> 00:33:51,029
Alys Zyril Perez.

581
00:33:51,372 --> 00:33:53,750
Can I call you Zy or Zyril?

582
00:33:54,417 --> 00:33:58,212
Only Tripp calls me Zy or Zyril.

583
00:33:58,588 --> 00:34:00,465
I know he’s here in New York, too.

584
00:34:01,007 --> 00:34:02,383
I wonder how he is.

585
00:34:02,954 --> 00:34:04,873
I hope you're doing alright, Tripp.

586
00:34:06,278 --> 00:34:07,279
What?

587
00:34:08,005 --> 00:34:09,005
Oh, nothing.

588
00:34:09,298 --> 00:34:10,966
Oh, I mean it's nothing.

589
00:34:11,558 --> 00:34:13,643
Uhm, you can just call me Alys.

590
00:34:13,852 --> 00:34:14,779
Alys.

591
00:34:14,803 --> 00:34:15,927
Nice to meet you, Alys.

592
00:34:15,928 --> 00:34:17,431
Nice to meet you too.

593
00:34:17,944 --> 00:34:19,116
Uhm, Karen?

594
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:20,141
Yeah?

595
00:34:20,470 --> 00:34:22,972
Can I ask for your FB account?

596
00:34:22,973 --> 00:34:26,268
So I can add you and we
can maybe become friends.

597
00:34:26,685 --> 00:34:28,383
You're so cute, Alys!

598
00:34:28,797 --> 00:34:30,611
You know, you're like my little sister.

599
00:34:31,197 --> 00:34:33,822
Yeah, just search me up.
The name's Karen Burmejo.

600
00:34:34,070 --> 00:34:35,113
Burmejo?

601
00:34:35,114 --> 00:34:35,907
Yeah.

602
00:34:35,908 --> 00:34:37,760
By any chance, are you Filipino?

603
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:38,785
Actually, I am!

604
00:34:38,788 --> 00:34:40,747
- I was actually born in the Philippines,
- I knew it.

605
00:34:40,748 --> 00:34:42,041
but raised here in the States.

606
00:34:42,394 --> 00:34:43,394
How about you?

607
00:34:43,401 --> 00:34:44,767
I was born and raised there.

608
00:34:44,769 --> 00:34:45,728
And now I'm here.

609
00:34:45,729 --> 00:34:47,313
And I badly wanna go back home.

610
00:34:47,589 --> 00:34:48,589
Aww.

611
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:50,464
You're such a cutie pie. Come here!

612
00:34:50,475 --> 00:34:51,976
Let me give you a hug.

613
00:34:52,966 --> 00:34:54,927
You know what, you got this, girl.

614
00:34:55,211 --> 00:34:56,337
Everything's gonna be fine.

615
00:34:56,595 --> 00:34:57,679
I promise you.

616
00:34:58,378 --> 00:34:59,796
Wait, why are you here?

617
00:35:00,225 --> 00:35:03,812
For work? School? Family drama?

618
00:35:04,813 --> 00:35:05,688
Studies.

619
00:35:05,689 --> 00:35:08,857
I'm currently studying at NYCU
and I'm taking advertising.

620
00:35:08,858 --> 00:35:10,067
Oh my gosh, that's so funny.

621
00:35:10,068 --> 00:35:11,361
I go there too!

622
00:35:11,906 --> 00:35:13,212
But I'm getting my Master's.

623
00:35:13,236 --> 00:35:14,571
Really, sister?

624
00:35:14,938 --> 00:35:16,965
Oh, is it okay if I call you sister?

625
00:35:16,978 --> 00:35:17,978
Sure.

626
00:35:19,138 --> 00:35:21,411
So does that mean you
can teach me sometimes?

627
00:35:21,418 --> 00:35:23,246
Of course, baby girl.

628
00:35:23,258 --> 00:35:25,263
When I'm free,
I'll teach you everything.

629
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:27,250
You've nothing to worry about.

630
00:35:27,517 --> 00:35:30,103
You know, you really
resemble my little sister.

631
00:35:30,297 --> 00:35:32,298
Then she must be really cute like me.

632
00:35:32,299 --> 00:35:33,987
She's so cute and fluffy!

633
00:35:33,994 --> 00:35:35,136
I wanna die!

634
00:35:36,052 --> 00:35:37,052
Sorry.

635
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:39,804
You know, I'm really hungry.
Do you wanna get lunch?

636
00:35:40,254 --> 00:35:43,465
Do you like Thai food?
I know this really good place.

637
00:35:44,353 --> 00:35:45,854
- Sure!
- Come on, let's go!

638
00:35:49,567 --> 00:35:52,820
Karen, this is actually
my first time eating in a Thai resto.

639
00:35:52,862 --> 00:35:53,862
- Hey.
- What?

640
00:35:54,405 --> 00:35:56,047
Can someone join your table?

641
00:35:56,071 --> 00:35:57,446
The place is packed.

642
00:35:57,447 --> 00:35:59,741
Uhm, sure. Whatever.

643
00:36:01,535 --> 00:36:02,536
- Oh, thank you.
- Sorry.

644
00:36:03,128 --> 00:36:04,129
It's weird.

645
00:36:04,755 --> 00:36:05,755
Uh...

646
00:36:07,549 --> 00:36:09,509
Uh, so the waiter told me
I can sit here?

647
00:36:09,510 --> 00:36:11,321
Oh, uhm. I have to take this call.

648
00:36:11,345 --> 00:36:12,221
I'll be right back.

649
00:36:12,222 --> 00:36:13,222
Okay!

650
00:36:19,728 --> 00:36:21,772
And you are?

651
00:36:25,548 --> 00:36:26,966
I'm Christofer Ann Palma.

652
00:36:27,878 --> 00:36:28,878
Palma?

653
00:36:29,362 --> 00:36:31,162
I wonder how this
person is related to Drake.

654
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:34,859
Well, there are lots of Palma in the world.

655
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:36,611
There are tons of Perez too.

656
00:36:36,848 --> 00:36:39,476
But we're not all related.

657
00:36:40,458 --> 00:36:42,168
Christofer Ann?

658
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:45,829
Hey! Don't laugh.

659
00:36:46,413 --> 00:36:47,790
Ann is from my grandmother.

660
00:36:48,831 --> 00:36:50,458
I'm her only grandkid so...

661
00:36:50,464 --> 00:36:53,169
Yeah, my name is Ann.
Whatever.

662
00:36:54,587 --> 00:36:56,297
Ann and he’s a guy.

663
00:36:57,048 --> 00:36:58,048
Huh?

664
00:36:59,139 --> 00:37:00,140
Are you Filipino?

665
00:37:01,976 --> 00:37:03,310
You're Filipino too?!

666
00:37:03,716 --> 00:37:07,100
Oh my gosh, fellow countrymen!
I can speak in Tagalog now!

667
00:37:08,679 --> 00:37:10,371
Hey, calm down.

668
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:11,563
You're so noisy.

669
00:37:11,576 --> 00:37:14,107
Sorry, I can’t help it.
I miss speaking in Tagalog.

670
00:37:14,118 --> 00:37:15,900
You speak Tagalog, as well.

671
00:37:15,905 --> 00:37:17,694
- True.
- You’re using English on me.

672
00:37:18,438 --> 00:37:19,022
Wait.

673
00:37:19,439 --> 00:37:20,857
You didn't shake my hand yet.

674
00:37:21,698 --> 00:37:22,699
What's your name?

675
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,034
Alys Zyril Perez.

676
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:27,954
Alys Perez?

677
00:37:28,335 --> 00:37:29,628
By any chance,

678
00:37:30,545 --> 00:37:32,005
is Drake your boyfriend?

679
00:37:33,635 --> 00:37:34,635
Oops.

680
00:37:37,733 --> 00:37:38,942
Let me see.

681
00:37:39,650 --> 00:37:41,759
I like what's going on in here.

682
00:37:41,773 --> 00:37:44,971
I think you should add more
to this side so it's not like...

683
00:37:45,555 --> 00:37:46,973
you know, all over the place.

684
00:38:01,861 --> 00:38:02,861
Hi!

685
00:38:03,196 --> 00:38:04,490
Are you Ms. Stinson?

686
00:38:04,708 --> 00:38:05,658
Yes, I am.

687
00:38:05,661 --> 00:38:06,662
Are you Ms. Perez?

688
00:38:06,846 --> 00:38:07,928
Yes, nice to meet you.

689
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:09,096
Nice to meet you.

690
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,496
I'm sorry, I still have jetlag.

691
00:38:10,501 --> 00:38:12,437
I just got back from New York.

692
00:38:12,461 --> 00:38:13,504
No worries.

693
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:16,603
So, where's the groom?

694
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:18,837
Oh, he's on his way.

695
00:38:18,838 --> 00:38:21,465
Sorry, he's just really busy.

696
00:38:26,012 --> 00:38:29,015
I'll show you the list of cake designs
that we have so we can proceed.

697
00:38:29,019 --> 00:38:30,019
- Okay?
- Sure.

698
00:38:30,025 --> 00:38:31,109
Make yourself at home.

699
00:38:31,112 --> 00:38:32,112
Thank you.

700
00:39:07,429 --> 00:39:11,449
Uh, Ms. Perez.
This is my groom, Drake.

701
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:13,856
Babe, this is Ms. Perez.

702
00:39:13,864 --> 00:39:15,896
She is the one making our cake.

703
00:39:22,131 --> 00:39:23,132
Hi, Alys.

704
00:39:53,242 --> 00:39:54,362
So where are you headed now?

705
00:39:54,660 --> 00:39:56,454
I'm about to leave the airport.

706
00:39:57,749 --> 00:39:58,749
I'm here.

707
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:01,357
Hurry up, I've been waiting since earlier.

708
00:40:02,108 --> 00:40:04,152
I'm almost there.

709
00:40:04,678 --> 00:40:05,929
I'm so excited to see you.

710
00:40:08,156 --> 00:40:09,157
Me too.

711
00:40:10,738 --> 00:40:11,739
Babe!

712
00:40:15,251 --> 00:40:16,252
Babe!

713
00:40:26,054 --> 00:40:27,508
- Welcome back!
- Wow!

714
00:40:27,517 --> 00:40:30,059
You brought flowers.

715
00:40:30,597 --> 00:40:31,806
Thank you!

716
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:34,432
How's Harvard?

717
00:40:34,891 --> 00:40:37,101
It was okay.
Piece of cake.

718
00:40:38,633 --> 00:40:40,176
Paris will be good for you, Zy.

719
00:40:40,526 --> 00:40:41,939
Especially now that you got
the course you wanted.

720
00:40:41,946 --> 00:40:42,986
So I’m sure you’ll ace it.

721
00:40:43,906 --> 00:40:46,367
I'm rooting for you, Zy.
I'm always rooting for you.

722
00:40:49,579 --> 00:40:50,579
Babe!

723
00:40:58,794 --> 00:41:00,128
Ms. Perez!

724
00:41:01,626 --> 00:41:02,127
Yes?

725
00:41:02,134 --> 00:41:03,134
You dropped this.

726
00:41:03,581 --> 00:41:05,667
Oh, geez. Thanks, sir.

727
00:41:06,821 --> 00:41:08,196
Oh my gosh, Alys.

728
00:41:08,197 --> 00:41:09,157
Who was that?

729
00:41:09,158 --> 00:41:10,366
Oh, it's nothing.

730
00:41:10,614 --> 00:41:12,282
I just dropped my passport.

731
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:13,930
Come on, Zy.

732
00:41:13,940 --> 00:41:15,191
You're so clumsy.

733
00:41:15,794 --> 00:41:17,256
Silly!

734
00:41:17,267 --> 00:41:19,363
I miss you already.

735
00:41:19,367 --> 00:41:22,790
Seriously, when I see you,
I'm going to hug you to death!

736
00:41:22,800 --> 00:41:23,884
I’m sorry, Zy.

737
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:25,274
There’s nothing I can do.

738
00:41:25,277 --> 00:41:26,695
You left me here.

739
00:41:27,077 --> 00:41:29,621
Now you’ll have to suffer with Tofer.

740
00:41:30,196 --> 00:41:32,365
Wow, thanks so much!

741
00:41:32,371 --> 00:41:35,076
My boyfriend is so kind!

742
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:36,784
Boyfriend.

743
00:41:37,745 --> 00:41:39,163
That sounds so nice.

744
00:41:41,308 --> 00:41:42,350
Seriously, Marco.

745
00:41:42,351 --> 00:41:44,227
We've been together for two years.

746
00:41:44,228 --> 00:41:46,522
You're still getting
giddy for me until now?

747
00:41:47,202 --> 00:41:48,245
What can I do?

748
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,341
My girlfriend is so pretty.

749
00:41:50,682 --> 00:41:51,682
Shut up!

750
00:41:52,158 --> 00:41:55,638
And because of that,
you're coming home right now!

751
00:41:55,662 --> 00:41:57,497
Please, please!

752
00:41:58,892 --> 00:41:59,892
I can't.

753
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:01,811
I need to do something here in New York.

754
00:42:02,008 --> 00:42:03,187
I need to close a deal.

755
00:42:05,262 --> 00:42:06,471
Fine.

756
00:42:06,862 --> 00:42:08,238
Do your best there, okay?

757
00:42:08,572 --> 00:42:10,573
I'll call you later when I get to the shop.

758
00:42:10,574 --> 00:42:11,574
Love you!

759
00:42:12,033 --> 00:42:13,173
Alright.

760
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:14,281
Love you more!

761
00:42:14,282 --> 00:42:16,784
Alright then, your boyfriend still
has something to do.

762
00:42:17,061 --> 00:42:18,854
Okay! Bye, boyfriend!
I love you!

763
00:42:18,879 --> 00:42:19,879
Bye, Zy!

764
00:42:29,556 --> 00:42:30,556
Oh!

765
00:42:31,443 --> 00:42:32,819
Welcome home, Perez!

766
00:42:33,629 --> 00:42:35,671
Why did you even come home too?

767
00:42:35,672 --> 00:42:36,756
Well, of course.

768
00:42:36,971 --> 00:42:38,639
Who'll watch over you?

769
00:42:41,016 --> 00:42:43,060
I don't need a babysitter, Tofer.

770
00:42:43,063 --> 00:42:45,520
I'm already 22 years old.

771
00:42:45,521 --> 00:42:48,483
And plus, I've been living alone
for four years.

772
00:42:48,489 --> 00:42:50,234
Are you freaking kidding me?

773
00:42:51,974 --> 00:42:53,184
Alys...

774
00:42:54,050 --> 00:42:57,053
Well, Tripp thinks differently.

775
00:43:01,129 --> 00:43:03,915
So, are you ready?

776
00:43:03,922 --> 00:43:06,500
Well, do I have a choice?

777
00:43:09,971 --> 00:43:11,931
Goodness, Perez.

778
00:43:25,103 --> 00:43:28,607
On the next episode of
Dating Alys Perez.

779
00:43:29,149 --> 00:43:31,902
Don't you have a crush
on Drake's girlfriend?

780
00:43:33,111 --> 00:43:36,073
You're on your usual
crazy self again.

781
00:43:36,573 --> 00:43:38,367
I'm in love with you again.

782
00:43:39,263 --> 00:43:40,264
You're nuts.

783
00:43:41,556 --> 00:43:43,239
I know!

784
00:43:43,263 --> 00:43:47,308
And I promised your girlfriend that
I'm never gonna flirt with you ever again!

785
00:43:47,309 --> 00:43:48,602
How are you and Kei?

786
00:43:49,422 --> 00:43:52,133
Bestie said they're roommates.

787
00:43:52,556 --> 00:43:53,808
Can you imagine?

788
00:43:54,100 --> 00:43:58,354
Out of everyone Alys could have
as a roommate, it’s Kei Chui!

789
00:44:00,549 --> 00:44:01,550
Tripp!

790
00:44:03,523 --> 00:44:05,900
Alys is nice. Drake is bad.

791
00:44:05,902 --> 00:44:07,654
Congratulations, you passed the test!

792
00:44:07,962 --> 00:44:09,505
Your flight's tomorrow afternoon.

793
00:44:09,856 --> 00:44:11,024
Drake!

794
00:44:11,029 --> 00:44:12,358
They’re not a good match, man!

795
00:44:12,362 --> 00:44:15,339
You and Alys are a better match, you know.

796
00:44:15,342 --> 00:44:18,053
Honestly, I'm a TripLys fan, you know!
